title: AEC Syndrome: Epidemiology and Population Prevalence
short_description: Clinical document describing the epidemiological characteristics of AEC syndrome, including gender distribution and population prevalence data.
long_description: This clinical research document provides epidemiological information about AEC syndrome, a rare genetic disorder. The document details that the condition affects males and females equally, with no gender predisposition. It emphasizes the rarity of the condition, noting that fewer than 100 cases have been documented in medical literature, and acknowledges that the exact incidence and prevalence rates in the general population remain unknown due to its extremely rare nature.
